00:04:52.030 --> 00:04:54.210
and reading about him in the newspapers.

00:04:54.210 --> 00:04:56.070
That's a reasonable and familiar way

00:04:56.070 --> 00:04:58.370
to learn about someone else.

00:04:58.370 --> 00:05:00.340
How about Barack Obama himself?

00:05:00.340 --> 00:05:03.430
Can he know himself through
seeing himself on television

00:05:03.430 --> 00:05:05.700
or reading about himself
in the newspapers?

00:05:05.700 --> 00:05:07.640
Presumably, he can and does

00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:10.210
learn some things about
himself in that way.

00:05:10.210 --> 00:05:12.320
He might learn about a
funny expression he makes

00:05:12.320 --> 00:05:13.980
by seeing Obama in the evening news.

00:05:13.980 --> 00:05:16.280
He might learn what his exact words were

00:05:16.280 --> 00:05:17.150
at a press conference

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:18.900
by reading the transcript the next day

00:05:18.900 --> 00:05:20.960
in the New York Times.

00:05:20.960 --> 00:05:22.110
But the writer makes it sound

00:05:22.110 --> 00:05:24.437
as if he is only aware
of Borges' very existence

00:05:24.437 --> 00:05:26.810
through these third person ways

00:05:26.810 --> 00:05:28.653
and that would be rather odd.

00:05:29.642 --> 00:05:32.750
It would not only be
odd but quite impossible

00:05:32.750 --> 00:05:35.440
for Borges to survive the writer,

00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:37.260
even if all that's meant by survival

00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:39.040
is living on as a literary figure.

00:05:39.040 --> 00:05:41.440
If Borges lives on in that
way, so will the writer,

00:05:41.440 --> 00:05:43.150
they're one in the same person.

00:05:43.150 --> 00:05:44.880
Other contradictions are only implied

00:05:44.880 --> 00:05:47.918
as if the writer likes
hourglasses, Stephenson

00:05:47.918 --> 00:05:48.751
and the taste of coffee

00:05:48.751 --> 00:05:51.223
in a less vain and artificial
way than Borges does.

00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:53.840
In following the writer's thoughts,

00:05:53.840 --> 00:05:55.310
we must to a certain extent,

00:05:55.310 --> 00:05:57.160
pretend that the writer is not Borges

00:05:58.040 --> 00:06:00.560
but if we think of it as just
a story about two people,

00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:01.770
one of whom reads about the other,

00:06:01.770 --> 00:06:02.960
shares some of his tastes,

00:06:02.960 --> 00:06:04.550
finds him pompous and annoying

00:06:04.550 --> 00:06:06.100
and yet somehow supports him,

00:06:06.100 --> 00:06:07.900
it loses its point.

00:06:07.900 --> 00:06:09.020
The interest of the story

00:06:09.020 --> 00:06:11.430
is the thoughts that the
writer has about himself,

00:06:11.430 --> 00:06:13.140
thoughts that are most naturally expressed

00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:14.720
in the forms of words usually reserved

00:06:14.720 --> 00:06:16.930
for talking about someone else.

00:06:16.930 --> 00:06:18.500
The writer is driven to these words

00:06:18.500 --> 00:06:20.980
not only because of some fugue state

00:06:20.980 --> 00:06:23.320
in which he has forgotten
that he is Borges

00:06:23.320 --> 00:06:26.513
but in order to express a
certain alienation he feels

00:06:26.513 --> 00:06:29.071
about what certain aspects of himself

00:06:29.071 --> 00:06:31.146
and certain achievements of his,

00:06:31.146 --> 00:06:33.120
how he feels about them,

00:06:33.120 --> 00:06:34.970
aspects and achievements he can convey

00:06:34.970 --> 00:06:36.673
by the use of the name Borges.

00:06:37.803 --> 00:06:41.034
To understand how Borges' words work,

00:06:41.034 --> 00:06:46.018
we need to distinguish
between two kinds of beliefs

00:06:46.018 --> 00:06:48.440
or more generally attitudes.

00:06:48.440 --> 00:06:50.110
But I'll say, just two kinds of beliefs

00:06:50.110 --> 00:06:52.360
our words can express about ourselves

00:06:52.360 --> 00:06:54.580
which I call self belief

00:06:54.580 --> 00:06:57.920
and belief about the
person you happen to be.

00:06:57.920 --> 00:06:59.580
Now, to make these distinctions,

00:06:59.580 --> 00:07:01.980
I shift to the second
interesting part of the talk,

00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:04.933
an anecdote that Ernst
Mach tells about himself.

00:07:06.040 --> 00:07:09.533
So the dean should like
this being a physicist.

00:07:12.110 --> 00:07:15.320
Mach, in the analysis
of sensations early on

00:07:15.320 --> 00:07:16.827
tells the following story about himself,

00:07:16.827 --> 00:07:18.720
"Not long ago," he writes,

00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:22.297
"after a trying railway journey by night

00:07:22.297 --> 00:07:23.557
"when I was very tired,

00:07:23.557 --> 00:07:25.361
"I got into an omnibus

00:07:25.361 --> 00:07:28.363
"just as another man
appeared at the other end.

00:07:29.330 --> 00:07:33.057
"What a shabby pedagogue that
is that has just entered,

00:07:33.057 --> 00:07:34.157
"thought I.

00:07:34.157 --> 00:07:37.600
"It was myself, opposite
me hung a large mirror."

00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:39.790
Mirrors they have in buses and cable cars

00:07:39.790 --> 00:07:41.010
so that when they're crowded,

00:07:41.010 --> 00:07:43.607
the conductors can keep track of everyone.

00:07:43.607 --> 00:07:45.657
"The physionomy of my class accordingly

00:07:45.657 --> 00:07:47.507
"was better known to me than my own."

00:07:48.367 --> 00:07:52.110
Now Mach acquired a belief at
the beginning of the episode

00:07:52.110 --> 00:07:54.254
that we can imagine him expressing as

00:07:54.254 --> 00:07:57.763
one, that man is a shabby pedagogue.

00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:01.080
By the end of the episode he has another

00:08:01.080 --> 00:08:03.380
which we can imagine him expressing as,

00:08:03.380 --> 00:08:04.853
I am a shabby pedagogue.

00:08:05.890 --> 00:08:07.420
And just for bookkeeping

00:08:07.420 --> 00:08:09.530
and to make it easier to
compare him with Borges,

00:08:09.530 --> 00:08:11.040
we'll imagine that he went on

00:08:11.040 --> 00:08:12.717
to make an obvious inference and say,

00:08:12.717 --> 00:08:15.190
"Mach is a shabby pedagogue."

00:08:15.190 --> 00:08:17.460
So we've got three ways of expressing

00:08:18.424 --> 00:08:21.272
something that's true if and only if,

00:08:21.272 --> 00:08:23.900
a single person, Mach
is a shabby pedagogue.

00:08:23.900 --> 00:08:26.220
Two expresses self knowledge

00:08:26.220 --> 00:08:27.833
or at least self belief.

00:08:29.500 --> 00:08:31.564
While one and three really don't

00:08:31.564 --> 00:08:34.240
and yet one and three are,

00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:36.030
in a perfectly clear sense,

00:08:36.030 --> 00:08:39.080
a case of Mach knowing
something about himself.

00:08:39.080 --> 00:08:41.310
For example, we think of one as being true

00:08:41.310 --> 00:08:43.820
because Mach implies that he was, in fact,

00:08:43.820 --> 00:08:45.390
a shabby pedagogue.

00:08:45.390 --> 00:08:47.210
If Mach's being a shabby pedagogue

00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:48.930
is what makes one true,

00:08:48.930 --> 00:08:50.450
then one was about Mach

00:08:50.450 --> 00:08:53.360
and expressed a belief about Mach.

00:08:53.360 --> 00:08:55.900
But one is not an
expression of self belief.

00:08:55.900 --> 00:08:58.850
One, remember, is that
man is a shabby pedagogue.

00:08:58.850 --> 00:09:02.010
Self belief would be, I
am a shabby pedagogue.

00:09:02.010 --> 00:09:05.630
Similar remarks apply to three.

00:09:05.630 --> 00:09:07.560
I shall say that three and one express

00:09:07.560 --> 00:09:10.980
beliefs about the person
Mach happens to be

00:09:10.980 --> 00:09:13.113
while two expresses self belief.

00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:16.546
To get a bit clearer
about the distinction,

00:09:16.546 --> 00:09:20.470
it would be helpful to elaborate
a little on Mach's case

00:09:20.470 --> 00:09:21.540
and number three.

00:09:21.540 --> 00:09:23.530
Suppose when he gets off the bus,

00:09:23.530 --> 00:09:26.270
Mach trips, falls and hits his head.

00:09:26.270 --> 00:09:28.930
For a day or two, he has amnesia.

00:09:28.930 --> 00:09:32.070
He can't remember his name
or what he does for a living.

00:09:32.070 --> 00:09:33.730
He reads the newspaper the next morning

00:09:33.730 --> 00:09:34.760
and in the gossip column,

00:09:34.760 --> 00:09:36.920
he encounters a story
about a shabby pedagogue

00:09:36.920 --> 00:09:39.187
seen on the bus the day before.

00:09:39.187 --> 00:09:40.657
"Shabby pedagogue turns out

00:09:40.657 --> 00:09:44.054
"to be famous scientist
Ernst Mach," it says.

00:09:44.054 --> 00:09:46.740
So Mach comes to have a belief

00:09:46.740 --> 00:09:48.745
he would express with three

00:09:48.745 --> 00:09:50.640
and that belief was true,

00:09:50.640 --> 00:09:52.350
if and only if, the person referred to

00:09:52.350 --> 00:09:54.310
by the newspaper as Ernst Mach

00:09:54.310 --> 00:09:55.470
is a shabby pedagogue

00:09:55.470 --> 00:09:56.930
and he is that person

00:09:56.930 --> 00:10:00.375
so in a sense, he comes to
have a belief about himself

00:10:00.375 --> 00:10:03.040
but only about the
person he happens to be,

00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:04.120
not really a self belief.

00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:06.110
But of course, ordinarily,

00:10:06.110 --> 00:10:07.990
the beliefs Mach expressed was one

00:10:07.990 --> 00:10:10.470
and expresses the next day with three

00:10:10.470 --> 00:10:12.210
would be integrated
with the sort of belief

00:10:12.210 --> 00:10:15.540
he expressed with two, the I expression,

00:10:15.540 --> 00:10:17.670
the I belief, the self belief.

00:10:17.670 --> 00:10:20.130
Ordinarily, the beliefs
we pick up about ourselves

00:10:20.130 --> 00:10:22.260
by looking in a mirror or
reading something about ourselves

00:10:22.260 --> 00:10:23.450
using our own name,

00:10:23.450 --> 00:10:26.540
are quickly added to our
stock of self beliefs

00:10:26.540 --> 00:10:28.930
but the point is this
really amounts to something,

00:10:28.930 --> 00:10:30.093
it's not trivial.

00:10:31.509 --> 00:10:34.070
It amounts to more than
the beliefs in question

00:10:34.070 --> 00:10:35.799
merely being about us.

00:10:35.799 --> 00:10:37.500
We could acquire the beliefs

00:10:37.500 --> 00:10:38.900
without, in the intuitive way,

00:10:38.900 --> 00:10:41.130
realizing that the beliefs we had

00:10:41.130 --> 00:10:43.040
are beliefs about us,

00:10:43.040 --> 00:10:45.409
they wouldn't be self beliefs.

00:10:45.409 --> 00:10:48.250
And I'm claiming that
when we get back to Borges

00:10:48.250 --> 00:10:49.730
this will be a useful distinction

